Work/life balance ⚖️

If you work with your family, you know how difficult it can be sometimes. You work 24/7, 7 days a week with no work/life balance. Because even during - especially during the holidays, when you’re all together, you’re talking the most about work. HOWEVER - there is nothing more rewarding. I feel so lucky I’m able to work with my mom. Most of my life I spent trying to pave my own way - working in marketing, advertising, and art. While I loved those jobs, clearly this is where I was meant to be. If you have the opportunity to work with your family, even for a summer or for a few days, I strongly suggest you take it. You’ll learn so much more about business AND your relationship ❤️ swipe for an example of how we communicate 😂

I’ve struggled with my body image and weight loss my whole life #wwsequencepartner.  You might remember the infamous “fat camp” I went to when I was on reality TV, and for years after I would try any weight loss fad, and nothing really worked until I found GLP-1 medications. Being on these medications for 8 years now, and finally happy with my weight - my focus has shifted from weight loss to maintenance - and living an overall healthy lifestyle.

Which is why I am so excited to partner with @joinsequence by WeightWatchers! Rather than looking at one piece of the puzzle like other doctors have in the past, they offer a comprehensive & holistic approach towards weight loss. In addition to prescribing a GLP-1, Sequence can really be your partner and your community with you on your journey (as opposed to when I started out and feeling lost). Sequence provides 1:1 nutrition and fitness consultations + personalized plans and lessons that include information on sleep and stress, making you feel comfortable and most importantly listened to.

I am so excited to start on this journey with Sequence (and you) in creating a healthier future for myself that doesn’t include yo-yo dieting or unhealthy habits. Whether you’ve wanted to start using a GLP1 medication or are curious what it’s like being on it long term I am here to answer any questions - and I’m excited to start this new chapter with you guys! Had the most inspiring day at the GLP-1 House by @weightwatchersclinic 💙 @weightwatchers brought together a dozen people from all different backgrounds, experiences, and perspectives. Some had just started using GLP-1s, and some have been on them for some time - but all of us have always struggled with weight loss, management,food noise, and obesity. It honestly felt like going to camp for a day with a little bit of therapy 😂 where everyone shared their own journey. Even though we had such different stories, there were so many similarities. Things we didn’t even realize were because of GLP-1s! Like how we no longer have that food noise controlling us. One other thing I didn’t realize until now was that I also don’t crave alcohol. Anyway…just wanting to say how appreciative I am for this experience and I hope to meet all of you wonderful people again. For someone with lots of social anxiety I started the day feeling so nervous and out of my comfort zone, but walked away with so many friends.

We’re always looking for sweet ways to eat protein. Try making these Strawberry Cottage Cheese Muffins with @allyshapiro—6 grams of protein for 1 muffin 🤩❤️🍓. #glp1house 
 
You’ll need: 
✨ 5/8 tsp of baking powder 
✨ 5/8 tsp of vanilla extract 
✨ 2/3 cup uncooked oats 
✨ 4 medium, pitted and coarsley chopped dates 
✨ 1/3 cup fat free cottage cheese 
✨ 1 large egg 
✨ 3 oz strawberries 

Instructions: ⁣
Preheat oven to 350. Microwave dates and 1 tbsp of water for 45 seconds, set aside. In a food processor, process cottage cheese until smooth. Add baking powder, vanilla, and eggs; process until well combined. Add the date mixture and oats; process until combined. Add 3/4 of strawberries and pulse to combine. Spoon batter evenly into the prepared muffin cups and top the batter with the remaining strawberry slices. Bake for about 30 minutes.⁣
⁣
